verses.roman:
hena-kāle kāśī-miśra, paḍichā,-dui jana
āsiyā karila prabhura caraṇa vandana

synonyms: hena-kāle—at this time; kāśī-miśra—Kāśī Miśra; paḍichā—the superintendent; dui jana—two persons; āsiyā—coming; karila—did; prabhura—of Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; caraṇa vandana—worshiping the lotus feet.
translation: At this time, Kāśī Miśra, along with the superintendent of the temple, came and offered his respects unto the lotus feet of Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu.
